            <noteGrp type="workDesc">
               <note type="description">Treatise on the nature of the materia prima, time, and the celestial spheres in terms reminiscent of IA’s teachings. According to Claude Addas, likely to be authentic and part of three short treatises, which have been edited by Abd al-Baqi Miftah.</note>
               <note type="biblioComments">Only two mss. mentioned by OY (see p. 269), neither of them with good provenance. Berlin 2960 is very late, and there is nothing on the work to indicate that it is by IA, except that it is part of collection of works, by IA and other Sufi authors. We have not managed to inspect the other, Ismail Saïb 1197. Also mss at Cairo Khedivial 6/90 (16368), Dar al-Kutub 1/246 (46) and Vienna, Kaiser 1910/3 and Mecca Haram 3939.</note>
